<h1>片</h1><p class=neha><span style="color:#000099;">piàn</span><span class=alesi>(pian4)</span> , <span style="color:#990000;">piān</span><span class=alesi>(pian1)</span> , <span style="color:#000099;">pàn</span><span class=alesi>(pan4)</span> <span class=lesi>// pronunciations of 片 in Mandarin Pinyin</span></p><h2>Basic information about 片</h2><div class=abo>
<p><b>Unihan definition:</b> <a href="/dictionary/slice" style="color:black;">slice</a>, <a href="/dictionary/splinter" style="color:black;">splinter</a>, <a href="/dictionary/strip" style="color:black;">strip</a>; rad. 91</p><p><b>Number of strokes:</b> 4<br><small>Examples of other characters consisting of 4 strokes: <a href="/character/不" title="bu4: no, not; un-; negative prefix">不</a>, <a href="/character/中" title="zhong1: central; center, middle; in the midst of; hit (target); attain">中</a>, <a href="/character/为" title="wei4: do, handle, govern, act; be">为</a>, <a href="/character/以" title="yi3: by means of; thereby, therefore; consider as; in order to">以</a>, <a href="/character/方" title="fang1: a square, rectangle; a region; local">方</a>, <a href="/character/天" title="tian1: sky, heaven; god, celestial">天</a>, <a href="/character/分" title="fen1: divide; small unit of time etc.">分</a>, <a href="/character/心" title="xin1: heart; mind, intelligence; soul">心</a>, <a href="/character/开" title="kai1: open; initiate, begin, start">开</a>, <a href="/character/从" title="cong2: from, by, since, whence, through">从</a></small></p><p><b>Radical:</b> <a href="/character/片" title="Kangxi radical 91">片</a>&nbsp;91.0</p><p><b>HSK level:</b> 3 <br><small>Other HSK 3 characters: <a href="/character/包" title="bao1: wrap, pack, bundle; package">包</a>, <a href="/character/史" title="shi3: history, chronicle, annals">史</a>, <a href="/character/乎" title="hu1: interrogative or exclamatory final particle">乎</a>, <a href="/character/查" title="cha2: investigate, examine, seek into">查</a>, <a href="/character/轻" title="qing1: light; easy, simple; gentle">轻</a>, <a href="/character/易" title="yi4: change; easy">易</a>, <a href="/character/除" title="chu2: eliminate, remove, except">除</a>, <a href="/character/须" title="xu1: must, have to, necessary">须</a>, <a href="/character/照" title="zhao4: shine, illumine, reflect">照</a>, <a href="/character/容" title="rong2: looks, appearance; figure, form